  "_about": "Ten Steps for the sulis-plugins-marketplace release-train Workflow, re-modelled to the trunk-based (main-only) shape (CH-01KT4K). The release is no longer a merge between branches — it is a bump + tag on the trunk. Each Step declares the IDEF0 contract (input_artifacts + output_artifacts + mechanism) plus the Tool it invokes (tool_ref) and the FailureModes it can recover from (handles_failures). Steps 1-2 cover recon + in-branch version-drift pre-flight (cross-branch ancestry drift no longer exists on a trunk). Step 3 computes the next version (composite — uses cumulative_tier then next_version Tools). Step 4 is the founder-confirmation gate (mechanism=human, MUC-007). Steps 5-10 execute the ship phase: bump version files, write the CHANGELOG entry, commit directly to main as the bot, tag + push, publish the GitHub Release, emit the Release entity. The five dev->main-PR Steps (preflight-cross-branch-drift, draft-pr-body-and-changelog, open-release-pr, wait-for-checks-and-mergeability, squash-merge) were deleted in the trunk re-model — there is no release PR. Schema: plugins/sulis/brain/compiled/foundation/step.schema.json (v1.2.0). Tenant + workflow ULIDs are deterministic and shared across every release-train canonical instance (see triggers.jsonld + failuremodes.jsonld _about for derivation). Step ordering is canonical (array position 0..9 = Step 1..10); for_workflow is an envelope-level relation per the brain Step schema (step→workflow modelled at the instance container, not per-Step). Envelope-level `excluded_from_yaml` declares Steps deliberately absent from release-on-merge.yml (gate-founder-confirmation = the founder's manual merge per MUC-007; publish-github-release = the downstream release-prod.yml on the v* tag); the drift detector reads this list and treats those Step names as expected absences rather than drift. This encoding lives at the envelope (not per-Step) because the brain Step schema sets unevaluatedProperties:false and rejects new Step-level fields — extending the foundation schema is a cross-repo concern out of scope here.",
  "captured_on": "2026-06-01",
  "excluded_from_yaml": [
    "gate-founder-confirmation",
    "publish-github-release"
  ],

